insider.com%2Fmanagers-burned-out-looking-for-new-jobs-more-than-subordinates-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverworked%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20others%20might%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-manage-your-boss-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enot%20be%20good%20managers%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20while%20relying%20on%20artificial%20intelligence%20for%20career%20inspo%20can%20be%20a%20move%20of%20desperation%2C%20it's%20also%20possible%20that%20the%20youngest%20segment%20of%20the%20workforce%20is%20onto%20something%3A%20It%20makes%20sense%20to%20turn%20to%20a%20tool%20like%20AI%20for%20career%20guidance%20as%20long%20as%20it's%20not%20the%20sole%20source%20of%20advice.%20That's%20according%20to%20Christopher%20G.%20Myers%2C%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faom.org%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAcademy%20of%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E%20scholar%20and%20associate%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20Johns%20Hopkins%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BChatGPT%20can%20synthesize%20vast%20quantities%20of%20generalized%20information%2C%20and%20that%20can%20be%20incredibly%20valuable%2C%20but%20it%20isn't%20the%20same%20as%20the%20sort%20of%20contextualized%20information%20that%20you%20get%20from%20a%20conversation%20with%20a%20manager%20or%20a%20mentor%20within%20your%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trick%20is%20getting%20that%20time%20with%20the%20boss%2C%20which%20can%20be%20hard.%20In%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgo.intoo.com%2Femployee-growth-development-report.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esurvey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%2062%25%20of%20Gen%20Z%20workers%20said%20they'd%20like%20to%20talk%20more%20about%20their%20career%20path%20but%20that%20their%20boss%20was%20often%20too%20busy.%20That%20might%20be%20one%20reason%20some%20young%20workers%20find%20it%20beneficial%20to%20hit%20up%20bots%20or%20turn%20to%20social%20media%20with%20career%20questions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20survey%20results%20were%20also%20notable%20because%20workers%20who%20felt%20at%20least%20%26quot%3Bsomewhat%26quot%3B%20supported%20by%20their%20manager%20were%20almost%20seven%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20state%20they'd%20made%20significant%20career%20progress%20in%20the%20past%20year%20than%20those%20who%20didn't%20get%20much%20help%20from%20the%20boss.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20tech%20becomes%20the%20head%20coach%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20workers'%20willingness%20or%20even%20preference%20for%20using%20tech%20as%20a%20means%20of%20getting%20ahead%20isn't%20new%2C%20Myers%20said.%20He%20pointed%20to%20search%20engines%20and%20MOOCs%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0massive%20open%20online%20courses%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0as%20some%20of%20the%20ways%20workers%20have%20for%20years%20leveled%20up%20their%20abilities.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20could%20kind%20of%20say%2C%20'Well%2C%20I%20get%20better%20skill-building%20from%20a%20YouTube%20tutorial%20than%20from%20my%20manager%2C'%26quot%3B%20Myers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20concern%2C%20beyond%20getting%20information%20that's%20not%20specific%20to%20an%20employer%2C%20would%20be%20if%20people%20rely%20too%20much%20on%20tech%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20question%20just%20becomes%20how%20do%20we%20make%20sure%20that%20folks%20aren't%20ignoring%20the%20conversation%20with%20their%20manager%20or%20managers%20aren't%20offloading%20responsibility%20for%20mentoring%20onto%20ChatGPT%2C%26quot%3B%20Myers%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20training%20budgets%20are%20often%20among%20the%20first%20things%20to%20get%20cut%20when%20employers%20hit%20a%20rough%20patch.%20That%20might%20have%20been%20what%20some%20employers%20did%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20Myers%20said.%20Those%20types%20of%20rollbacks%20can%20leave%20younger%20workers%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20feeling%20like%20their%20career%20progression%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20stalling.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20s