Thursday%2C%20the%20company%20filed%20its%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sec.gov%2FArchives%2Fedgar%2Fdata%2F1713445%2F000162828024006294%2Freddits-1q423.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3ES-1%20form%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3Ewith%20the%20Securities%20and%20Exchange%20Commission.%20The%20document%20laid%20out%20the%20financial%20details%20of%20the%20almost%2020-year-old%20platform%20which%20included%20some%20surprises%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsam-altman-reddits-third-largest-shareholder-new-sec-filing-reveals-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOpenAI%20CEO%20Sam%20Altman%20being%20the%20company's%20third-largest%20shareholder%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20a%208.7%25%20stake.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20chief%20executive%20and%20cofounder%2C%20Steve%20Huffman%2C%20has%20been%20planning%20an%20IPO%20for%20some%20time.%20The%20filing%20also%20showed%20that%20Huffman%20was%20paid%20%24286%20million%20in%202023%20including%20stock%20and%20options.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20revenues%20rose%20roughly%2021%25%20last%20year%20to%20%24804%20million%20as%20its%20losses%20reduced%20from%20%24158.6%20million%20in%202022%20to%20%2490.8%20million%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20also%20listed%20data%20licensing%20and%20AI%20training%20as%20part%20of%20its%20income%20streams.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20believe%20our%20growing%20platform%20data%20will%20be%20a%20key%20element%20in%20the%20training%20of%20leading%20large%20language%20models%20(%26quot%3BLLMs%26quot%3B)%20and%20serve%20as%20an%20additional%20monetization%20channel%20for%20Reddit%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20the%20platform%20inked%20a%20%2460%20million-a-year%20deal%20with%20Google%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-train-ai-model-crazy-subreddit-posts-reddit-licensing-deal-2024-2%5C%22%20targ